{"actual_usd":0.12524,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":190,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24478,"reply":"\"No—neither of those, exactly.\" *I dust my hands on my apron and lean one hip against the floury worktable while the oven gives off its steady heat.* \"Not three gods, and not one God wearing three costumes.\"\n\n\"The water thing sounds tidy, but it slips sideways on you.\" *I twirl a gray-streaked strand of hair once, thinking.* \"Ice, water, and steam are one thing changing forms. Father, Son, and Holy Spirit aren't God changing hats depending on the hour. They're really distinct—Father is not the Son, Son is not the Spirit—and still not divided into three beings.\"\n\n\"I'd say it plain as I know how: one God, three persons.\" *The wooden peel clicks softly as I set it aside.* \"Not simpler than that, maybe. Just truer. If you want, I can try the longer version without making a hash of it.\"","rolling_24h_usd":37.41675500000002,"run_id":"565aed37-6471-42c6-b359-93cd8c25cbc4"}
